                <h1>Education: The Foundation of Martin Luther King Jr.'s Legacy</h1>
                <p>Martin Luther King Jr. emphasized the importance of education in achieving equality and justice. He believed that education empowers individuals to challenge oppression and promotes social change. King himself was a highly educated man with a doctorate, advocating for the transformative power of knowledge in American society.</p>
